                                        Calling Flow From Apex
                                      ----------------------------
  Process of Calling Flow From Apex: - 
                                        1). Create a Autolaunched flow --> create record using resources.
                                        2). once flow created, pass the resouces value from apex refer the below code.
                              Note: - {if you want to return value from flow to apex use assignment in the flow}.

                    public class P_Call_ApexToFlow {
                        public static void createAccountThroughFlow() {
                            Map<String,Object> passToFlow = new Map<string,Object>();
                            passToFlow.put('AccountName' , 'Munnan coming From Apex to Flow'); // key as resource of the flow
                            passToFlow.put('AnnualRevenueNumber' , '1234567890'); // key as resouce of the flow
                            try {
                                    // calling process
                                 Flow.Interview.create_Acount_From_Apex myFlow = new Flow.Interview.create_Acount_From_Apex(passToFlow);
                                 myFlow.start();
                                String returnedValue = myFlow.accountId; 
                                 System.debug('Flow executed successfully==='+returnedValue);
                                
                            }
                            catch(Exception e) {
                                System.debug('Exception occured=='+e.getMessage());
                            }
                                
                        }
                        
                    
                    }
